summary: This is an FBI FD-302 form documenting a proffer interview conducted at the Southern District of New York on September 10, 2019. The document is heavily redacted and contains garbled text, making specific details about the interviewee, the interviewers, and the information provided unreadable. It is part of the investigation into Jeffrey Epstein (File 90A-NY-3151227).

keyFacts: A proffer interview was conducted on September 10, 2019, at the SDNY office in New York City.
The interview was attended by multiple law enforcement officials, including Assistant United States Attorneys and an FBI Special Agent, but their names are redacted.
The document is an FBI FD-302 form, which is a summary of an investigative interview.
The document is associated with the Jeffrey Epstein investigation (File 90A-NY-3151227).
The substantive text of the interview notes is heavily redacted and/or garbled, preventing extraction of specific factual claims.
